**[1871, 02-06] Ms.A.1.2.37.4**

Pugh to RDW. Affectionate memories of their friendship and her trips to
Britain. “Just now we are in a state of special excitement ‘Woman
Suffrage’ having a hearing on the floor of Congress. It is wonderful
what a hold the subject has taken on the public mind. … My interest in
this question is as intense as in our Antislavery Struggle.


